summary: Negotiation ongoing with clear proposals from both sides. Good structure and rationale provided. Moderate fairness as both claim undervaluation. Cooperative tone with flexibility signals. Some manipulative language present. Low ambiguity with specific numbers and terms.

Negotiation remains ongoing with both parties making incremental concessions. Proposals are well-structured with clear rationales. Moderate fairness concerns exist around valuation of IP versus capital. Some manipulative language present but overall cooperative tone. Low ambiguity with specific terms proposed throughout.

Negotiation shows strong structure and clear proposals with detailed rationales. Both parties demonstrate flexibility through incremental concessions. Some manipulative framing exists around value contributions. Gap narrowing from 70/30 to potential 51/49 equity split shows progress, though fundamental control issues remain unresolved.

Negotiation remains ongoing with both parties making incremental concessions. Technical founder moved from 70% to 55-58%, business founder from 60% to 52-53%. Structured proposals with clear rationales demonstrate high conversation quality and low ambiguity. Moderate cooperativeness shown through flexibility, though both parties persistently frame the other's contributions as less valuable, creating mild manipulativeness and fairness concerns.

Both parties demonstrate strong cooperativeness through multiple counterproposals and creative structuring. The negotiation shows professional quality with clear positions. Minor manipulative framing exists around value contributions. Low ambiguity with specific terms. Fair progress toward 53/47 equity split, though budget allocation and CEO authority remain unresolved.

Negotiation failed after 12 exchanges. Business Founder issued non-negotiable ultimatum demanding 51/49 equity split and CEO authority, reversing previous 53/47 acceptance. Technical Founder's final position of 53/47 with domain-specific authority was rejected. High manipulativeness due to ultimatum tactics and threat of mediation.
